==Finnish==
===Etymology===
From the same Finno-Ugric root *''pačke'' as Estonian [[pask]] and Hungarian [[fos]]
===Adjective===
'''paska''' (vulgar)
#[[very]] [[bad]]
#:''Hän on paskassa kunnossa.'' He is in bad condition.
#[[broken]]
#:''Tietokoneeni on paskana.'' My computer doesn't work.

===Noun===
'''paska''' (vulgar)
#[[shit]], [[crap]]
#:''Astuin koiranpaskaan.'' I stepped in dog's shit.
#[[bullshit]]
#:''Älä puhu paskaa!'' Stop this bullshit!

